WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
[Amit Varma]: I.V.M.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.740
[Amit Varma]: by putting an end to Article 370.

00:00:32.740 --> 00:00:34.860
[Amit Varma]: But what is this argument even?

00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:39.960
[Amit Varma]: The Kashmir issue is at one level a geopolitical dispute between India and Pakistan, and even

00:00:39.960 --> 00:00:45.540
[Amit Varma]: there the nature and incentives and priorities of both sides have changed over the years

00:00:45.540 --> 00:00:47.720
[Amit Varma]: and so has what they have been fighting for.

00:00:47.720 --> 00:00:52.380
[Amit Varma]: It is also a moral question about the right of the people of Kashmir to decide their own

00:00:52.380 --> 00:00:53.500
[Amit Varma]: destiny.

00:00:53.500 --> 00:00:58.000
[Amit Varma]: But even there nuances exist, and one man's freedom fighter is another man's terrorist.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:03.840
[Amit Varma]: There is also the question of means and ends, where even a nationalist who agrees with India's

00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:07.320
[Amit Varma]: ends may disagree with the means used to get there.

00:01:07.320 --> 00:01:11.080
[Amit Varma]: The troubled history of Kashmir definitely does not end here.

00:01:11.080 --> 00:01:16.720
[Amit Varma]: All we can do at this moment is take a look back in time and take stock.

